---
import { PEOPLE } from '@helpers/constants';
import { cn } from '@helpers/utils';
---

<section class="flex flex-col gap-24 px-4 pb-48">
	<article class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-[1512px] grid-cols-12 gap-x-4">
		<div class="col-span-2 flex flex-col gap-5 font-medium">
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-2" data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.1s">
				<p class="text-base-5">Font</p>
				<p>Helvetica Neue</p>
			</div>

			<div class="flex flex-col gap-2" data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.22s">
				<p class="text-base-5">Stack</p>
				<ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
					<li>Astro</li>
					<li>Svelte</li>
					<li>Tailwind CSS</li>
					<li>TypeScript</li>
					<li>Motion</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-span-5 col-start-5 flex flex-col gap-5 font-medium text-pretty">
			<p data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.1s">
				This site exists to present work without interference. It avoids trends, unnecessary
				movement, and decorative systems that compete with content.
			</p>

			<p data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.22s">
				The design relies on typography, spacing, and structure. Inter was chosen for its neutrality
				and clarity across screens—quiet, dependable, and designed to disappear. Layouts are simple by
				intent; interaction is restrained and purposeful.
			</p>

			<p data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.34s">
				The site is built with a static-first mindset, prioritising performance, accessibility, and
				long-term maintainability. Tooling is modern but conservative. Every dependency earns its
				place.
			</p>

			<p data-colophon-info style="--delay: 1.46s">
				Over the years, I've been influenced by family, teachers, colleagues, designers, writers,
				musicians, and public figures—some personally, some from a distance—who have shaped how I
				think, work, and build.
			</p>

			<ul
				class={cn('mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-base-5')}
				data-colophon-info
				style="--delay: 1.58s"
			>
				{PEOPLE.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
			</ul>
		</div>
	</article>
</section>

<script>
	import { introState } from '@helpers/intro-state';

	document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', () => {
		if (introState.hasPlayed) return;
		document.querySelectorAll('[data-colophon-info]').forEach((el) => {
			el.classList.add('info-animate');
		});
	});
</script>

<style>
	@keyframes fadeInUp {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			filter: blur(10px);
			transform: translateY(20px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			filter: blur(0px);
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	.info-animate {
		opacity: 0;
		animation: fadeInUp 0.7s var(--ease-smooth) forwards;
		animation-delay: var(--delay, 0s);
	}
</style>
